<paragraph blockId="62.[192,1440,195,539]" pageId="62" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis box="[240,370,483,507]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="61">Etymology</emphasis>
—This species is named 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blahnik &amp; Holzenthal" authorityYear="2017" box="[678,809,483,507]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Mortoniella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="62" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="furcula">
<emphasis box="[678,809,483,507]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="61">M. furcula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as a diminutive form of the Latin 
<emphasis box="[1251,1316,483,507]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="61">furca</emphasis>
, meaning fork, and referring to the forked apex of the ventromesal process of the inferior appendages.
</paragraph>
